text: Why do developers always reboot their laptop? Because they want to 'refresh' the issue.

A developer walked into a library and asked the librarian, "Do you have any books on JavaScript and databases?" The librarian replied, "I think I have something on SQL here somewhere, but it'll probably require a few async calls to load."
Why do developers name their functions with unnecessary abbreviations and suffixes? Because they're trying to branch out from the norm, but end up forking their own sanity.
